So GG to you for not reading the whole thing or understanding the point I was trying to get across.  I never once said that the person reading the word should be responsible for not feeling offended, I simply said that they shouldn't be shocked to see it.  If they are, they should say something as well.  I am a firm believer that people should be careful of what they say and mindful of others (you should talk to me in RL sometime... I'm very tactful with what I say and how I say it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )... but I'm also a firm believer that in many situations people need to take what they see with a grain of salt.  As Auri said you need to look at the context the term is being used in.  If someone says &quot;We're gunna rape Xegony tonight!&quot; it's very different than someone saying &quot;AFK to rape my girlfriend.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pedidustyboots>Pedi Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 734<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 3:19 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You're just not getting it.</span><hr size=1> Rombus, I absolutely agree -- there is definitely a way to express yourself without saying curse words.<br>
<br>
I don't know who wrote this in forum rules -- I always thought it was you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>... Besides.. a foul mouth doesn't make you look very impressive.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That statement applies 100% to words that aren't necessary. &quot;Retard,&quot; &quot;gay,&quot; &quot;rape,&quot;and so on. There are plenty of slang words that don't involve degrading someone or something in some fashion.<br>
<br>
Swear words + the above words have the enormous potential to offend. Not everyone is offended by those, but that doesn't make it any less significant. Any time we decide to swear or express ourselves in this manner, we take the risk of coming across as junivelle and thus appearing as unimpressive to other people.<br>
<br>
Whenever I decide to swear, I accept the responsibility of possibily offending someone and belittling my own position. I know that and I accept that. <br>
<br>
If someone calls me a cunt and I'm not offended by it, does that make it OK? No. That word is meant to be hurtful. &quot;Gay&quot; and &quot;rape&quot; is meant to be hurtful. You can use them in a manner that is not meant to be hurtful, sure, but there's always the chance that someone is going to be hurt by it anyway. Why bother?<br>
<br>
People have the right to go ahead and use these words, but in all honesty, they aren't going to look very impressive, are they? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Tyrant<br><br>Owned by Ikeya<BR>Destroying EverWars...<BR><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Rombus</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 7088<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 3:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You're just not getting it.</span><hr size=1> You're right, and I agree with what you just said for the most part.  The problem here though is that in games like EverQuest you're dealing with a wide range of people of all ages.  A 12 y/o boy most likely does not understand what you're saying.  When he says &quot;wow, we raped Soandso&quot; or &quot;man, that was gay&quot; do you think he's using those terms literally?  Of course not.  When you go into &quot;worlds&quot; like this you have to enter them with an open mind and literally allow yourself to take more.  In a way you do have to take some responsibility for yourself not being offended.  Go ahead Girndel, jump all over me for that one but it is the truth.<br>
