I for one would not tolerate someone using half the terms they do in game in real life.  I give my brother dirty looks when he swears around me.  In game though I realize that people let go and use terms differently, and not literally. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grindel>Grindel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>High Priest of HLS</span><br>  Posts: 1849<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 3:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Misusing the term 'Rape'</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I never once said that the person reading the word should be responsible for not feeling offended, I simply said that they shouldn't be shocked to see it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  ....mmmkay.  First, I read every word you wrote.  I quoted the parts I deemed relevant.  I assure you, I did quite well in reading comprehension when I was a kid and I understand your entire position.  You're stating over and over again that people should get over it, you don't mean anything 'bad' when you callously use the term rape, even in the face of all the other people who have posted in this thread that the term used in-game does everything from puzzle them to send a shiver and reflexive physical impulse through their RL body.  Since you don't mean anything bad when you say it others should just accept it in the non-mean spirit you're saying it in.  <br>
